condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :External Auditor | Description :The Recipient shall recruit no later than six (6) months after the EffectiveDate, the external auditor pursuant to terms of reference satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :01-Jun-2015

Finance Agreement :Financial Management Software | Description :The Recipient shall, no later than two (2) months after theEffective Date, acquire, install and thereafter maintain an accounting software acceptable to the Association, for the Project. |Due Date :01-Feb-2015

Finance Agreement :Financial Management | Description :The Recipient shall recruit no later than one (1) month after effectivenessa financial management expert and an accountant on a competitive basis and pursuant to terms of reference satisfactory to theAssociation. | Due Date :01-Jan-2015

Finance Agreement :Internal Auditor | Description :The Recipient shall recruit no later than four (4) months after the EffectiveDate, an internal auditor, whose qualifications and experience and terms of reference shall be acceptable to the Association. | DueDate :01-Apr-2015

Finance Agreement :Procurement | Description :The Recipient shall recruit no later than two (2) months after effectiveness aprocurement expert on a competitive basis and pursuant to terms of reference satisfactory to the Association . | Due Date:01-Feb-2015

Finance Agreement :Project Coordination Unit | Description :The Recipient, through MEFP, shall maintain, throughout theimplementation of the Project, a Project Coordination Unit (PCU). | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Steering Committee | Description :The Recipient, through MEFP, shall establish not later than three (3)months after Effective Date and thereafter maintain, throughout the implementation of the Project and in a manner satisfactory tothe Association, a Project Steering Committee chaired by the minister of the MEFP or his representative. | Due Date :02-Mar-2015
